        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">&#8226; <strong>[SQJ 2020]</strong> Cross-project bug type prediction based on transfer learning. <CitationCount paperId="mrf-JvkAAAAJ:u-x6o8ySG0sC" /></li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <Section title="Research Projects">
      <ul style="list-style: none;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">
          <Badge variant="project">Algorithm Lead</Badge> <strong>Automated Test Generation for Safety-Critical Embedded Software</strong> (2020 – 2023)
          <p style="margin-left: 1.25rem; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 0.25em;">
            Utilized <strong>State Charts</strong> to model intricate system behaviors and developed <strong>Search-based Algorithms</strong> to automatically identify test paths and generate test cases.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">
          <Badge variant="project">Core Researcher</Badge> <strong>Reliability Simulation Platform for Distributed Network Systems</strong> (2021 – 2023)
          <p style="margin-left: 1.25rem; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 0.25em;">
            Developed a comprehensive simulation platform applying <strong>Markov Chains</strong> to model system states for real-time reliability prediction.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">
          <Badge variant="project">Core Researcher</Badge> <strong>Automated Testing for Deep Learning Object Detection Systems</strong> (2019 – 2022)
          <p style="margin-left: 1.25rem; font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 0.25em;">
            Built an automated testing framework for <strong>YOLO</strong> using <strong>Metamorphic Testing</strong> with custom image transformation operators.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">
